rlm-cd-sub [FD_ARGS...]

Pick a subdirectory under the current directory via fzf and cd
into it. Useful when zoxide's `zi` is no help because the target
directory has never been visited and isn't in zoxide's database.

Directories are enumerated with `fd -t d`, which honors
`.gitignore` and skips hidden directories by default. Any extra
arguments are passed straight through to `fd`, so you can scope
the search with patterns or pass flags like `-H` (include
hidden) or `-I` (ignore .gitignore).

EXAMPLES
  cds                # pick any subdirectory under cwd
  cds -H             # include hidden directories
  cds models         # filter to paths matching "models"

REQUIRES
  fd, fzf

Aliases: cd-sub, cds
